s Queen Mother for nearly half a century. Even more influentially, it is the name of her daughter  Queen Elizabeth II  (  b. 1926 )."],"variants":[{"name":"Elisabeth","meanings":["The spelling of   Elizabeth   used in the Authorized Version of the New Testament, and in most modern European languages. This was the name of the mother of John the Baptist (Luke 1:60). Etymologically, the name means ‘God is my oath’, and is therefore identical with <i>Elisheba</i>, the name of the wife of Aaron according to the genealogy at Exodus 6:23. The final element seems to have been altered by association with Hebrew <i>shabbāth</i> ‘Sabbath’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Elizabeth Neufmarche was born on 16 September 1415, in Bisham, Berkshire, England. She had at least 1 son with John Huchyn. She died on 18 June 1448, in her hometown, at the age of 32, and was buried in Bisham, Berkshire, England."},"et":{"16 September 1415–18 June 1448":"16. september 1415–18. juuni 1448","1410–1480":"1410–1480","1430–1480":"1430–1480","1415–1448":"1415–1448","1448":"1448","1415":"1415","16 September 1415":"16. september 1415","18 June 1448":"18. juuni 1448","1410":"1410","1430":"1430","1480":"1480","Camborne, Cornwall, England":"Camborne, Cornwall, England","Bisham, Berkshire, England":"Bisham, Berkshire, England"},"fi":{"16 September 1415–18 June 1448":"16. syyskuuta 1415–18. kesäkuuta 1448","1410–1480":"1410–1480","1430–1480":"1430–1480","1415–1448":"1415–1448","1448":"1448","1415":"1415","16 September 1415":"16. syyskuuta 1415","18 June 1448":"18. kesäkuuta 1448","1410":"1410","1430":"1430","1480":"1480","Camborne, Cornwall, England":"Camborne, Cornwall, England","Bisham, Berkshire, England":"Bisham, Berkshire, England"},"fr":{"16 September 1415–18 June 1448":"16 septembre 1415–18 juin 1448","1410–1480":"1410–1480","1430–1480":"1430–1480","1415–1448":"1415–1448","1448":"1448","1415":"1415","16 September 1415":"16 septembre 1415","18 June 1448":"18 juin 1448","1410":"1410","1430":"1430","1480":"1480"